FREDERIC H. MAYERSON Frederic Mayerson is the Founder and Principal of The Frederic H. Mayerson  Group. He also is the Chairman and Ma﻿naging General Partner of Maywic Select Investments, a diversified investment firm. ​For the last 35 years, Fred has been involved in ventures focusing on consumer goods, communications, restaurants, toys and juvenile products, outsourcing, and corporate services - including Chi-Chi’s Mexican Restaurants, Build-a-Bear Workshop, Cap Toys and numerous others.  He has founded and acquired ownership in a number of companies, public and private. Fred also has owned and managed prime office, shopping center, and retail space and continues to be active in real estate. He was Chairman of United Sports Ventures, an owner of minor league baseball and hockey teams that won six championships.  He has co-produced twelve Tony Award winning Broadway musicals and a Pulitzer Prize-Winning drama. Throughout his career he has served on the Boards of Directors of several companies, public and private.    A graduate of the University of Michigan Law School with an undergraduate degree from Miami University, he received a Fellowship to the World Court in The Hague and practiced law in New York City before returning to Cincinnati to begin his business career.  He is a member of several professional and charitable organizations, especially those concerning children and education.  Fred's affiliations include: Director of U.S. Bank Board of Advisors, Trustee of the Mayerson Foundation, Member of The League of American Theatres and Producers, and Trustee of the Robert F. Kennedy Center for Human Rights, and Member of the Advisors of the Korey Stringer Institute of the National Football League.  He has run the Montreal Marathon, raced as a licensed NASCAR driver, and continues to enjoy and compete in a wide range of other sporting activities.





CHAD WICKChad Wick has been a CEO of commercial banks, large non-profit organizations, and a national foundation for the past 35 years.  As founding president and CEO of KnowledgeWorks Foundation, Chad has been recognized by former Secretary of Education Richard Riley as one of America’s most important leaders in education.  Chad built a major relationship with the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation and created the fastest growing high school network in the country, New Tech Network, with over 150 schools in 20 states.  In his business career, Chad organized and led the private buyout of Southern Ohio Bank and the sale of Student Loan Funding Corp to SallieMae.   Chad received his BS degree from the University of Cincinnati and MBA with high honors from Thunderbird Graduate School.  He served as president of the Mayerson Company, a diversified real estate and investment enterprise, and has served on numerous boards as a board member as well as president and CEO including: Ameritrust of Cincinnati, Southern Ohio Bank, Shawnee Life Insurance Co., RISE Learning Solutions, KnowledgeWorks and board member of ACT, Inc., Student Loan Funding Corp., ChoiceCare (Humana/Ohio), and Mount Vernon. Chad is a veteran of the U.S. Air Force and has participated in the Army War College’s Strategic Leadership Forum at Columbia University.  He has received honorary Doctorates from both the University of Cincinnati and Youngstown State University.  Chad is an avid cyclist and has cycled across America.





LAWRENCE HORWITZLawrence.Horwitz@maywic.comLarry coordinates deal flow, analysis and staff activity. He has founded and grown several companies including a financial services company serving medical and allied health professionals, national and international restaurant chains, and a direct-selling women’s apparel company. He has served as Chief of Staff at the Walnut Group, and has been a friend and colleague of Fred Mayerson for over 20 years.Larry has served as a director and trustee of various civic and performing arts organizations including the National Endowment for the Arts. His entrepreneurial endeavors include: re-establishing U.S. commerce with The People’s Republic of China in 1971 and an attempt to purchase the Berlin Wall in 1989.He was an Associate Professor of Entrepreneurship and Management at the University of Cincinnati Lindner College of Business and a faculty member at Thomas More College in Kentucky.  Larry has a BA in Foreign Affairs from the University of Cincinnati and an MBA from the Harvard Business School.















 
BRIAN SHIMKOBrian Shimko is responsible for analyzing and evaluating new and existing portfolio companies. Prior to joining Maywic, he was a Manager of Mergers and Acquisitions at EY and responsible for assisting companies with transactions and providing Finance department insights during an integration or divestiture. He began his career at GE in several roles in finance over the course of 9 years including the Financial Management Program and the Corporate Audit Staff. Brian earned an Economics degree at Fordham University and also has an M.B.A. from the University of Michigan’s Ross School of Business
 

















 
CLIFFORD NORRIS​Clifford began his 25 year career in business as a consultant for Development Specialists, a financial consulting firm, in Chicago and then transitioned into owning and operating various businesses. He has successfully and consistently steered businesses to successful exits including Lumber Yards and Medical lasers.  Recently, he was on the senior management team of a $50 MM medical equipment company that was acquired by a private equity firm. Based in Chicago, Cliff works in business development for Maywic, generating deal flow and supporting the portfolio companies. Cliff supports Elevarte, a community – based organization which uses arts as a portal for creative youth. Cliff earned an MBA from the Depaul University and a BS from University of Wisconsin.  
 







​﻿LAKSH KHURANALaksh is an Associate at Maywic where he is responsible for Financial, Research and Deal flow analysis.Prior to Maywic, he co-founded and operated as the Chief Financial Officer and Director of Sales at Sustain-a-Watt Energy Solutions LLC, which was rated among the top 10 startups in the Greater Cincinnati area before the company’s strategic exit.Laksh earned his BBA degree from New Delhi, India and graduated from the University of Cincinnati with his MBA and a graduate certificate in entrepreneurship. 




CLARK SCHAEFER HACKETTClark Schaefer Hackett has six locations and is one of the 60 largest CPA and advisory firms in the U.S.  Clark Schaefer Hackett provides services in audit and assurance, benefit plan consulting, financial consulting, forensic and litigation support, individual and business tax, and valuation and transaction services.  Clark Schaefer Hackett is the accountant of record for Maywic Select Investments and its fund and currently provides accounting, financial consulting, and tax services on behalf of the fund.

































